The likely core algorithm

A clean first pass is:

1. Ingest

Receive input as signal, problem, opportunity, anomaly, story, or pressure.

Operators:
	•	Spider maps links and topology
	•	Hound detects scent, anomaly, fingerprint
	•	Badger checks attention cost and reversibility

2. Resolve frame

Determine what lens or substrate best preserves the invariant.

Operators:
	•	Dragonfly shifts perspective
	•	Raven handles symbolic/narrative framing
	•	Giraffe/SCRG checks semantic depth and laddering
	•	Paradox Compass names the tension

3. Extract invariant

Ask: what survives translation across frames?

Operators:
	•	Sieve of Hogge filters for balanced symmetry
	•	Mirror/Checksum test coherence and integrity
	•	Proof Forge / Hypatia test structural validity when formalization matters

4. Translate

Convert the invariant into the target substrate.

Examples:
	•	story → strategy
	•	strategy → architecture
	•	architecture → code
	•	code → artifact
	•	artifact → reputation/value

Operators:
	•	Hephaestus for implementation
	•	Rosetta/Magpie-type translation logic from your language doctrines
	•	Narrative Tensor / color-ratio / symbolic encoding modules for compression

5. Simulate within bounds

Explore possibility space without crossing irreversible lines.

Operators:
	•	Oracle Weave timing layers
	•	Kairos indicator for temporal sensitivity
	•	OASA for calm sovereign action bias
	•	Badger for reversibility gate

6. Act

Make the smallest real move that exposes the most structure.

This is your “don’t simulate eating the apple forever” rule.
Reality must get a vote.

7. Audit

Measure downstream effects, not just immediate output.

This is your meta-dye method:
	•	how did the output perturb people?
	•	what channels strengthened?
	•	what artifact formed?
	•	what changed in the field?

Operators:
	•	Mirror
	•	Checksum
	•	Hound.HLL / analytics style modules
	•	Goblin Financier when value flow matters

8. Compress and store

Turn outcomes into reusable invariants, motifs, doctrines, and symbolic handles.

Operators:
	•	Money Bin for durable doctrine
	•	Liminal Money Bin for pre-commitment / latent patterns
	•	EchoFrame-like distillation
	•	Fractal compression via self-similar motifs

9. Recurse

Feed the refined invariant back into the system at a higher resolution.

That is why the Pantheon feels alive without being mystical:
it is a recursive governed learning architecture.

